sprint: S06
track: C
task: C1
title: "feat(search): multibrand part-number collision — correct brand attribution in results"
repos: [crop-search-hono]
priority: high
refs:
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("this will be the first time that our search will now be multibrand...
    a part number can be the same for two brands potentially")
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("search is going to be critical because it's going to be much more
    complicated when we're not using just the New Holland data set")
  - Dan — assigned owner of search; needs to be briefed on this requirement
requires: [BUN_HONO_CLOUDRUN]

impact: |
  When a user searches a part number that exists for both Ferris and New Holland,
  the search must surface both results with clear brand labeling. A result shown
  under the wrong brand erodes customer trust and causes wrong-part orders.
  With V2 adding 4 brands, this scenario becomes likely (common mower deck parts
  share part numbers across manufacturers).

description: |
  Pre-conditions:
  - Brief Dan on this requirement via the green-team channel (non-code action —
    Vova to provide agenda; team to update Dan on multibrand search gap before coding).

  Current state:
  - `/api/search` returns `manufacturer_codes` per part row (already present in
    PG response).
  - The CROP-front search results page renders manufacturer badges — verify these
    are populated for Ferris/Ventrac/McHale parts (not just NHL).

  Investigation:
  1. Search a known PN that appears in both NHL and one of the new brands.
  2. Check: does the response `manufacturer_codes` array contain multiple brand codes?
  3. Check: does CROP-front's search result card display all brand codes, or only the first?
  4. Check: does the brand facet in `/api/filters` include Ferris/Ventrac/McHale
     (requires `MANUFACTURER_FILTER_ENABLED=true`)?

  If manufacturer_codes is already correct in PG response (likely — data comes from
  parts.manufacturer_codes column which is populated per-brand), the fix may be purely
  in CROP-front's rendering of multi-manufacturer results.

  If PG-side: verify `search_parts_ranked()` returns non-NHL brand rows when
  non-NHL brand data is present in the DB (check with Alex on data pipeline status).

scope:
  in:
    - Audit: verify manufacturer_codes in /api/search response for Ferris parts
    - Fix: if manufacturer_codes is empty/wrong for non-NHL brands, identify the
      SQL gap (likely a JOIN on manufacturer_codes array field)
    - Verify: CROP-front brand facet shows Ferris/Ventrac when their parts are present
    - Document: the specific PN collision scenarios found (for Dan's reference)
  out:
    - Redesigning the search UI (CROP-front changes tracked separately)
    - Changing the search ranking algorithm
    - Data ingestion for new brands (Vova/Alex pipeline)

invariants:
  - Never filter out valid results to avoid collision — show all, label correctly
  - brand-safety.ts cross-contamination guard must apply to all brands, not only CNH family
  - No per-request PG hits for brand mapping — use vocabulary cache

acceptance:
  - Search a part number present in multiple brands → response manufacturer_codes
    contains all matching brand codes (not just the first)
  - CROP-front search result card shows all brand codes for multi-brand parts
  - Ferris brand facet appears in `/api/filters` results when Ferris data is in DB
  - No regression in existing NHL search behavior

dep: A1 (Marcrest in BRAND_REGISTRY needed for complete brand coverage)
output: src/routes/search.ts audit + fix (if needed) + docs note for Dan
